## Mindbrain Memory System

This project uses Mindbrain for persistent memory. Use the `mb` CLI to interact with it.

### Commands
- `mb context -f <files> -t "<task>"` — Get relevant memories for your current task
- `mb save "<title>" -t <type>` — Save a note (types: user, feedback, project, reference, codebase, debug)
- `mb search "<query>"` — Search existing notes
- `mb mine --dry-run` — Extract notes from past conversations

### When to Save
- After user corrections → `mb save "..." -t feedback`
- After fixing bugs → `mb save "..." -t debug`
- After architecture decisions → `mb save "..." -t project`
